3. AI/ML Core Components

3.1 Machine Learning Architecture

3.1.1 Multi-Model Ensemble Approach

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              ENSEMBLE PREDICTION ENGINE              │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐ │
│  │  CNN Model   │  │  RNN/LSTM    │  │ Transformer │ │
│  │ (Pattern     │  │ (Temporal    │  │ (Contextual │ │
│  │  Detection)  │  │  Analysis)   │  │  Analysis)  │ │
│  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬──────┘ │
│         │                  │                  │        │
│  ┌──────▼──────┐  ┌──────▼──────┐  ┌───────▼──────┐ │
│  │ Feature     │  │ Sequence    │  │ Attention    │ │
│  │ Extraction  │  │ Prediction  │  │ Weights      │ │
│  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬───────┘ │
│         └─────────────────┼─────────────────┘        │
│                    ┌──────▼──────┐                   │
│                    │  Meta-      │                   │
│                    │  Learner    │                   │
│                    │  (XGBoost)  │                   │
│                    └──────┬──────┘                   │
│                           │                          │
│                    ┌──────▼──────┐                   │
│                    │  Final      │                   │
│                    │  Prediction │                   │
│                    │  &          │                   │
│                    │  Confidence │                   │
│                    │  Score      │                   │
│                    └─────────────┘                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

3.1.2 Specialized ML Models

Model 1: Vulnerability Pattern Recognition (CNN-based)

```
Architecture:           Custom 12-layer CNN
Training Data:          500,000+ vulnerability instances
Accuracy:               94.2% on unseen patterns
Specialization:         Zero-day vulnerability identification
Input:                  Network traffic, application logs, code snippets
Output:                 Vulnerability classification with confidence score
```

Model 2: Attack Path Prediction (Graph Neural Network)

```
Architecture:           Graph Convolutional Network (GCN)
Training Data:          10,000+ attack graphs
Accuracy:               91.7% path prediction accuracy
Specialization:         Multi-step attack simulation
Input:                  Network topology, service dependencies
Output:                 Probabilistic attack graphs
```

Model 3: Threat Intelligence Correlation (Transformer-based)

```
Architecture:           BERT-based transformer
Training Data:          5TB+ threat intelligence data
Accuracy:               96.3% correlation accuracy
Specialization:         Cross-source intelligence fusion
Input:                  CVE data, exploit DB, dark web feeds
Output:                 Threat actor attribution, campaign identification
```

Model 4: Risk Scoring Engine (XGBoost Ensemble)

```
Architecture:          Gradient boosted trees
Training Data:         1,000,000+ historical breach data points
Accuracy:              98.1% risk prediction
Specialization:        Business impact assessment
Input:                 Vulnerability data, asset value, exploit availability
Output:                Risk score (1-1000), remediation priority
```

3.2 Natural Language Processing Capabilities

3.2.1 Security Documentation Analysis

· Automatic CVE Understanding: Extracts technical details from CVE descriptions
· Exploit Code Comprehension: Analyzes proof-of-concept code for applicability
· Research Paper Processing: Extracts novel attack techniques from academic papers
· Social Media Monitoring: Identifies emerging threats from security community discussions

3.2.2 Conversational AI Interface

```
User: "What's the most critical vulnerability in our WordPress deployment?"
VULNHUNTER: "Based on analysis of your WordPress 5.8.2 installation:
1. CVE-2022-21661: SQL Injection (CVSS 9.8) - Critical
   • 42% of similar installations exploited in last 90 days
   • Public exploit available: ExploitDB ID 51003
   • Recommendation: Update to WordPress 5.8.3 immediately

2. CVE-2022-21664: XSS in Media Library (CVSS 8.8) - High
   • 18% exploitation rate in wild
   • Requires authentication
   • Recommendation: Apply patch or disable upload functionality"
```

3.3 Reinforcement Learning for Attack Simulation

3.3.1 Autonomous Attack Agent

```
State Space:           Network configuration, service states, security controls
Action Space:          Exploit selection, privilege escalation, lateral movement
Reward Function:       + Points for discovering vulnerabilities
                       - Points for detection by security tools
                       ++ Points for critical system access
Training Method:       Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO)
Convergence:           85% success rate after 1M training episodes
```

3.3.2 Adversarial Training

· Generates novel attack techniques through self-play
· Tests security controls against synthetic adversaries
· Improves detection models through adversarial examples
· Simulates advanced persistent threats (APT) behavior

