5. Deployment Models

5.1 Deployment Options

5.1.1 Software as a Service (SaaS)

```
Advantages:
• Zero infrastructure management
• Automatic updates and scaling
• Pay-per-use pricing model
• Global availability (99.95% SLA)
• Built-in compliance certifications

Technical Specifications:
• Multi-tenant architecture with data isolation
• Global CDN for scanning performance
• 256-bit encryption at rest and in transit
• SOC 2 Type II, ISO 27001 certified
• GDPR, CCPA compliant
```

5.1.2 On-Premises Deployment

```
Advantages:
• Complete data sovereignty
• Air-gapped environment support
• Custom integration capabilities
• No external network dependencies
• Regulatory compliance requirements

Technical Requirements:
• Minimum: 8 vCPUs, 32GB RAM, 500GB storage
• Recommended: 16 vCPUs, 64GB RAM, 1TB SSD
• Network: 1Gbps+ connectivity
• OS: Ubuntu 20.04 LTS, RHEL 8+, Windows Server 2019+
• Container Runtime: Docker 20.10+, Kubernetes 1.23+
```

5.1.3 Hybrid Deployment

```
Advantages:
• Sensitive data kept on-premises
• Leverages cloud scalability
• Flexible deployment options
• Disaster recovery capabilities
• Cost optimization

Architecture:
• Control plane in cloud
• Scanning engines on-premises
• Encrypted data synchronization
• Unified management console
• Flexible licensing models
```

