7. Ethical & Legal Framework

7.1 Ethical Guidelines

7.1.1 Core Ethical Principles

```
Principle 1: Authorization First
• Never scan without explicit written authorization
• Respect scope boundaries defined in engagement agreement
• Immediate cessation upon request

Principle 2: Non-Destructive Operation
• All testing is non-disruptive by default
• Read-only operations unless explicitly authorized
• Safety mechanisms prevent accidental damage

Principle 3: Data Privacy & Confidentiality
• All findings encrypted end-to-end
• Data retention policies configurable by organization
• GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA compliant data handling

Principle 4: Transparency & Accountability
• Complete audit trail of all actions
• Explainable AI decisions with reasoning
• Regular third-party security audits

Principle 5: Responsible Disclosure
• Coordinated vulnerability disclosure process
• 90-day vendor notification period
• Public disclosure only after patch availability
```

